From {{inh|ja|ojp|sort=いさな|-}}.  Found in the ''{{w|Man'yōshū}}'' completed some time after 759 CE,<ref>{{RQ:Manyoshu|13|3335}}, text available online [http://jti.lib.virginia.edu/japanese/manyoshu/Man13Yo.html#3335 here]</ref> often with the spelling {{m|ja||鯨魚|lit=whale fish}}.

From cognate ''isa'' above, suffixed with {{m|ja|魚|tr=-na||fish}}.<ref name="KDJ">{{R:Kokugo Dai Jiten}}</ref><ref name="DJR">{{R:Daijirin}}</ref> Sometimes spelled as {{ja-l|勇魚}}.

